api_list.name: getProduct
api_list.description: Gets the product id and webhook url of the account.
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://maytapi-whatsapp.p.rapidapi.com/product"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "maytapi-whatsapp.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())

api_list.name: backup
api_list.description: Backups the material needed for opening the same chat screen for the current phone number. This call is useful when the  session is active and also the status of the session is active. Later, the response information can be used to open  the chat screen with the `POST restore` call.

required_parameters.name: phone_id
required_parameters.description: Id of the phone in the active session

api_list.name: logout
api_list.description: Logouts the number from the current session and converts the screen to qr-code screen.

required_parameters.name: phone_id
required_parameters.description: Id of the phone in the active session

api_list.name: setWebhook
api_list.description: Sets the webhook url. Webhook is used for directing the incoming messages and some changes in the session.
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://maytapi-whatsapp.p.rapidapi.com/setWebhook"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "maytapi-whatsapp.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.post(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())

api_list.name: setAckPreference
api_list.description: Sets the acknowledge notification preference to true or false. If it is set to true, then every acknowledge message of the delivered messages are sent to the webhook address if a webhook address is available. Otherwise, no acknowledgement is sent to the webhook.
